---
// Static editorial content for BrightFunded
// Supports multiple sections via the `section` prop
interface Props {
  section: string;
  fallbackBody?: string;
}
const { section, fallbackBody } = Astro.props;
---

{/* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
{/* CHALLENGES SECTION                                                  */}
{/* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
{section === "challenges" && (
<div class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700">

  <!-- Overview -->
  <p class="mb-4">
    To get a BrightFunded trading account you need to work through a traditional two step evaluation process. They keep things simple with just one model with a default 80% profit share, but you can choose an account size between $5K and $200K, with fees ranging from <strong>&euro;55 to &euro;975</strong> without addons.
  </p>
  <p class="mb-4">
    The rules are easy to follow — in Step 1 you need to reach an <strong>8% profit target</strong>, then Step 2 it drops to <strong>5%</strong>. At both steps risk requirements are the same, with a <strong>5% daily drawdown</strong> and <strong>10% overall</strong>. The daily permitted loss (5%) is calculated from the highest balance or equity recorded at <strong>end of day (EOD high-watermark)</strong> for new accounts. At step 1 and 2 you'll need to trade for a minimum of 5 days unless you buy the add-on, and each trade must stay open for at least <strong>1 minute</strong> to count as a trading day. There's no maximum days or time limit.
  </p>
  <p class="mb-8">
    BrightFunded does let you trade news during the evaluation, with no restrictions, which is a massive perk not offered by many prop firms. But it is worth noting once you become a funded trader (Funded Star Account), there is a <strong>10-minute window</strong> (5 minutes before and 5 minutes after) around significant news events where trading is prohibited.
  </p>

  <!-- ─── Challenge Fee Table ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Challenge Accounts</h3>
  <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-slate-200 mb-8">
    <table class="w-full text-sm whitespace-nowrap">
      <thead class="bg-slate-800 text-xs font-semibold text-white uppercase tracking-wide">
        <tr>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left">Account Size</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-right">Challenge Fee</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-right">Phase 1 Target</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-right">Phase 2 Target</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-right">Max Daily Loss</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-right">Max Total Drawdown</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100">
        <tr class="bg-white">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">$5,000</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-900">&euro;55</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">8% ($400)</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">5% ($250)</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">5% ($250)</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">10% ($500)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-slate-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">$10,000</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-900">&euro;95</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">8% ($800)</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">5% ($500)</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">5% ($500)</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">10% ($1,000)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-white">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">$25,000</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-900">&euro;195</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">8% ($2,000)</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">5% ($1,250)</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">5% ($1,250)</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">10% ($2,500)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-slate-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">$50,000</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-900">&euro;295</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">8% ($4,000)</td>
